name: calendar
title: Calendar API
description: Manipulates events and other calendar data.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

parameters.name: userIp
parameters.desc: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

fields.name: event
fields.desc: A global palette of event colors, mapping from the color ID to its definition. An event resource may refer to one of these color IDs in its color field. Read-only.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Type of the resource ("calendar#colors").

fields.name: updated
fields.desc: Last modification time of the color palette (as a RFC3339 timestamp). Read-only.

fields.name: calendar
fields.desc: A global palette of calendar colors, mapping from the color ID to its definition. A calendarListEntry resource refers to one of these color IDs in its color field. Read-only.

fields.name: locked
fields.desc: Whether this is a locked event copy where no changes can be made to the main event fields "summary", "description", "location", "start", "end" or "recurrence". The default is False. Read-Only.

fields.name: originalStartTime
fields.desc: For an instance of a recurring event, this is the time at which this event would start according to the recurrence data in the recurring event identified by recurringEventId. Immutable.

fields.name: start
fields.desc: The (inclusive) start time of the event. For a recurring event, this is the start time of the first instance.

fields.name: visibility
fields.desc:
Visibility of the event. Optional. Possible values are:  
- "default" - Uses the default visibility for events on the calendar. This is the default value. 
- "public" - The event is public and event details are visible to all readers of the calendar. 
- "private" - The event is private and only event attendees may view event details. 
- "confidential" - The event is private. This value is provided for compatibility reasons.

fields.name: attachments
fields.desc:
File attachments for the event. Currently only Google Drive attachments are supported.
In order to modify attachments the supportsAttachments request parameter should be set to true.
There can be at most 25 attachments per event,

fields.name: attendeesOmitted
fields.desc: Whether attendees may have been omitted from the event's representation. When retrieving an event, this may be due to a restriction specified by the maxAttendee query parameter. When updating an event, this can be used to only update the participant's response. Optional. The default is False.

fields.name: end
fields.desc: The (exclusive) end time of the event. For a recurring event, this is the end time of the first instance.

fields.name: id
fields.desc:
Opaque identifier of the event. When creating new single or recurring events, you can specify their IDs. Provided IDs must follow these rules:  
- characters allowed in the ID are those used in base32hex encoding, i.e. lowercase letters a-v and digits 0-9, see section 3.1.2 in RFC2938 
- the length of the ID must be between 5 and 1024 characters 
- the ID must be unique per calendar  Due to the globally distributed nature of the system, we cannot guarantee that ID collisions will be detected at event creation time. To minimize the risk of collisions we recommend using an established UUID algorithm such as one described in RFC4122.
If you do not specify an ID, it will be automatically generated by the server.
Note that the icalUID and the id are not identical and only one of them should be supplied at event creation time. One difference in their semantics is that in recurring events, all occurrences of one event have different ids while they all share the same icalUIDs.

fields.name: endTimeUnspecified
fields.desc: Whether the end time is actually unspecified. An end time is still provided for compatibility reasons, even if this attribute is set to True. The default is False.

fields.name: recurringEventId
fields.desc: For an instance of a recurring event, this is the id of the recurring event to which this instance belongs. Immutable.

fields.name: reminders
fields.desc: Information about the event's reminders for the authenticated user.

fields.name: overrides
fields.desc: If the event doesn't use the default reminders, this lists the reminders specific to the event, or, if not set, indicates that no reminders are set for this event. The maximum number of override reminders is 5.

fields.name: useDefault
fields.desc: Whether the default reminders of the calendar apply to the event.

fields.name: source
fields.desc: Source from which the event was created. For example, a web page, an email message or any document identifiable by an URL with HTTP or HTTPS scheme. Can only be seen or modified by the creator of the event.

fields.name: title
fields.desc: Title of the source; for example a title of a web page or an email subject.

fields.name: url
fields.desc: URL of the source pointing to a resource. The URL scheme must be HTTP or HTTPS.

fields.name: status
fields.desc:
Status of the event. Optional. Possible values are:  
- "confirmed" - The event is confirmed. This is the default status. 
- "tentative" - The event is tentatively confirmed. 
- "cancelled" - The event is cancelled.

fields.name: updated
fields.desc: Last modification time of the event (as a RFC3339 timestamp). Read-only.

fields.name: extendedProperties
fields.desc: Extended properties of the event.

fields.name: private
fields.desc: Properties that are private to the copy of the event that appears on this calendar.

fields.name: shared
fields.desc: Properties that are shared between copies of the event on other attendees' calendars.

fields.name: guestsCanSeeOtherGuests
fields.desc: Whether attendees other than the organizer can see who the event's attendees are. Optional. The default is True.

fields.name: hangoutLink
fields.desc: An absolute link to the Google+ hangout associated with this event. Read-only.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Type of the resource ("calendar#event").

fields.name: description
fields.desc: Description of the event. Optional.

fields.name: guestsCanModify
fields.desc: Whether attendees other than the organizer can modify the event. Optional. The default is False.

fields.name: recurrence
fields.desc: List of RRULE, EXRULE, RDATE and EXDATE lines for a recurring event, as specified in RFC5545. Note that DTSTART and DTEND lines are not allowed in this field; event start and end times are specified in the start and end fields. This field is omitted for single events or instances of recurring events.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of the resource.

fields.name: organizer
fields.desc: The organizer of the event. If the organizer is also an attendee, this is indicated with a separate entry in attendees with the organizer field set to True. To change the organizer, use the move operation. Read-only, except when importing an event.

fields.name: email
fields.desc: The organizer's email address, if available. It must be a valid email address as per RFC5322.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The organizer's Profile ID, if available. It corresponds to theid field in the People collection of the Google+ API

fields.name: self
fields.desc: Whether the organizer corresponds to the calendar on which this copy of the event appears. Read-only. The default is False.

fields.name: displayName
fields.desc: The organizer's name, if available.

fields.name: summary
fields.desc: Title of the event.

fields.name: transparency
fields.desc:
Whether the event blocks time on the calendar. Optional. Possible values are:  
- "opaque" - The event blocks time on the calendar. This is the default value. 
- "transparent" - The event does not block time on the calendar.

fields.name: anyoneCanAddSelf
fields.desc: Whether anyone can invite themselves to the event (currently works for Google+ events only). Optional. The default is False.

fields.name: privateCopy
fields.desc: Whether this is a private event copy where changes are not shared with other copies on other calendars. Optional. Immutable. The default is False.

fields.name: creator
fields.desc: The creator of the event. Read-only.

fields.name: displayName
fields.desc: The creator's name, if available.

fields.name: email
fields.desc: The creator's email address, if available.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The creator's Profile ID, if available. It corresponds to theid field in the People collection of the Google+ API

fields.name: self
fields.desc: Whether the creator corresponds to the calendar on which this copy of the event appears. Read-only. The default is False.

fields.name: gadget
fields.desc: A gadget that extends this event.

fields.name: title
fields.desc: The gadget's title.

fields.name: type
fields.desc: The gadget's type.

fields.name: width
fields.desc: The gadget's width in pixels. The width must be an integer greater than 0. Optional.

fields.name: display
fields.desc:
The gadget's display mode. Optional. Possible values are:  
- "icon" - The gadget displays next to the event's title in the calendar view. 
- "chip" - The gadget displays when the event is clicked.

fields.name: height
fields.desc: The gadget's height in pixels. The height must be an integer greater than 0. Optional.

fields.name: iconLink
fields.desc: The gadget's icon URL. The URL scheme must be HTTPS.

fields.name: link
fields.desc: The gadget's URL. The URL scheme must be HTTPS.

fields.name: preferences
fields.desc: Preferences.

fields.name: htmlLink
fields.desc: An absolute link to this event in the Google Calendar Web UI. Read-only.

fields.name: iCalUID
fields.desc:
Event unique identifier as defined in RFC5545. It is used to uniquely identify events accross calendaring systems and must be supplied when importing events via the import method.
Note that the icalUID and the id are not identical and only one of them should be supplied at event creation time. One difference in their semantics is that in recurring events, all occurrences of one event have different ids while they all share the same icalUIDs.

fields.name: location
fields.desc: Geographic location of the event as free-form text. Optional.

fields.name: sequence
fields.desc: Sequence number as per iCalendar.

fields.name: attendees
fields.desc: The attendees of the event. See the Events with attendees guide for more information on scheduling events with other calendar users.

fields.name: colorId
fields.desc: The color of the event. This is an ID referring to an entry in the event section of the colors definition (see the  colors endpoint). Optional.

fields.name: created
fields.desc: Creation time of the event (as a RFC3339 timestamp). Read-only.

fields.name: guestsCanInviteOthers
fields.desc: Whether attendees other than the organizer can invite others to the event. Optional. The default is True.

fields.name: method
fields.desc:
The method used by this reminder. Possible values are:  
- "email" - Reminders are sent via email. 
- "sms" - Reminders are sent via SMS. These are only available for G Suite customers. Requests to set SMS reminders for other account types are ignored. 
- "popup" - Reminders are sent via a UI popup.

fields.name: minutes
fields.desc: Number of minutes before the start of the event when the reminder should trigger. Valid values are between 0 and 40320 (4 weeks in minutes).

fields.name: nextPageToken
fields.desc: Token used to access the next page of this result. Omitted if no further results are available, in which case nextSyncToken is provided.

fields.name: nextSyncToken
fields.desc: Token used at a later point in time to retrieve only the entries that have changed since this result was returned. Omitted if further results are available, in which case nextPageToken is provided.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of the collection.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of rules on the access control list.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Type of the collection ("calendar#acl").

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of the resource.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Identifier of the ACL rule.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Type of the resource ("calendar#aclRule").

fields.name: role
fields.desc:
The role assigned to the scope. Possible values are:  
- "none" - Provides no access. 
- "freeBusyReader" - Provides read access to free/busy information. 
- "reader" - Provides read access to the calendar. Private events will appear to users with reader access, but event details will be hidden. 
- "writer" - Provides read and write access to the calendar. Private events will appear to users with writer access, and event details will be visible. 
- "owner" - Provides ownership of the calendar. This role has all of the permissions of the writer role with the additional ability to see and manipulate ACLs.

fields.name: scope
fields.desc: The scope of the rule.

fields.name: type
fields.desc:
The type of the scope. Possible values are:  
- "default" - The public scope. This is the default value. 
- "user" - Limits the scope to a single user. 
- "group" - Limits the scope to a group. 
- "domain" - Limits the scope to a domain.  Note: The permissions granted to the "default", or public, scope apply to any user, authenticated or not.

fields.name: value
fields.desc: The email address of a user or group, or the name of a domain, depending on the scope type. Omitted for type "default".

fields.name: description
fields.desc: Description of the calendar. Optional.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of the resource.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Identifier of the calendar. To retrieve IDs call the calendarList.list() method.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Type of the resource ("calendar#calendar").

fields.name: location
fields.desc: Geographic location of the calendar as free-form text. Optional.

fields.name: summary
fields.desc: Title of the calendar.

fields.name: timeZone
fields.desc: The time zone of the calendar. (Formatted as an IANA Time Zone Database name, e.g. "Europe/Zurich".) Optional.

fields.name: comment
fields.desc: The attendee's response comment. Optional.

fields.name: email
fields.desc: The attendee's email address, if available. This field must be present when adding an attendee. It must be a valid email address as per RFC5322.

fields.name: optional
fields.desc: Whether this is an optional attendee. Optional. The default is False.

fields.name: responseStatus
fields.desc:
The attendee's response status. Possible values are:  
- "needsAction" - The attendee has not responded to the invitation. 
- "declined" - The attendee has declined the invitation. 
- "tentative" - The attendee has tentatively accepted the invitation. 
- "accepted" - The attendee has accepted the invitation.

fields.name: additionalGuests
fields.desc: Number of additional guests. Optional. The default is 0.

fields.name: displayName
fields.desc: The attendee's name, if available. Optional.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The attendee's Profile ID, if available. It corresponds to theid field in the People collection of the Google+ API

fields.name: organizer
fields.desc: Whether the attendee is the organizer of the event. Read-only. The default is False.

fields.name: resource
fields.desc: Whether the attendee is a resource. Read-only. The default is False.

fields.name: self
fields.desc: Whether this entry represents the calendar on which this copy of the event appears. Read-only. The default is False.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of the resource.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: The id of the user setting.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Type of the resource ("calendar#setting").

fields.name: value
fields.desc: Value of the user setting. The format of the value depends on the ID of the setting. It must always be a UTF-8 string of length up to 1024 characters.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: Etag of the collection.

fields.name: items
fields.desc: List of user settings.

fields.desc: Type of the collection ("calendar#settings").

fields.desc: Token used to access the next page of this result. Omitted if no further results are available, in which case nextSyncToken is provided.

fields.name: nextSyncToken
fields.desc: Token used at a later point in time to retrieve only the entries that have changed since this result was returned. Omitted if further results are available, in which case nextPageToken is provided.

fields.name: backgroundColor
fields.desc: The main color of the calendar in the hexadecimal format "#0088aa". This property supersedes the index-based colorId property. To set or change this property, you need to specify colorRgbFormat=true in the parameters of the insert, update and patch methods. Optional.

fields.name: defaultReminders
fields.desc: The default reminders that the authenticated user has for this calendar.

fields.name: etag
fields.desc: ETag of the resource.

fields.name: hidden
fields.desc: Whether the calendar has been hidden from the list. Optional. The default is False.

fields.name: summary
fields.desc: Title of the calendar. Read-only.

fields.name: summaryOverride
fields.desc: The summary that the authenticated user has set for this calendar. Optional.

fields.name: timeZone
fields.desc: The time zone of the calendar. Optional. Read-only.

fields.name: accessRole
fields.desc:
The effective access role that the authenticated user has on the calendar. Read-only. Possible values are:  
- "freeBusyReader" - Provides read access to free/busy information. 
- "reader" - Provides read access to the calendar. Private events will appear to users with reader access, but event details will be hidden. 
- "writer" - Provides read and write access to the calendar. Private events will appear to users with writer access, and event details will be visible. 
- "owner" - Provides ownership of the calendar. This role has all of the permissions of the writer role with the additional ability to see and manipulate ACLs.

fields.name: foregroundColor
fields.desc: The foreground color of the calendar in the hexadecimal format "#ffffff". This property supersedes the index-based colorId property. To set or change this property, you need to specify colorRgbFormat=true in the parameters of the insert, update and patch methods. Optional.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc: Type of the resource ("calendar#calendarListEntry").

fields.name: colorId
fields.desc: The color of the calendar. This is an ID referring to an entry in the calendar section of the colors definition (see the colors endpoint). This property is superseded by the backgroundColor and foregroundColor properties and can be ignored when using these properties. Optional.

fields.name: description
fields.desc: Description of the calendar. Optional. Read-only.

fields.name: notificationSettings
fields.desc: The notifications that the authenticated user is receiving for this calendar.

fields.name: notifications
fields.desc: The list of notifications set for this calendar.

fields.name: primary
fields.desc: Whether the calendar is the primary calendar of the authenticated user. Read-only. Optional. The default is False.

fields.name: selected
fields.desc: Whether the calendar content shows up in the calendar UI. Optional. The default is False.

fields.name: deleted
fields.desc: Whether this calendar list entry has been deleted from the calendar list. Read-only. Optional. The default is False.

fields.name: id
fields.desc: Identifier of the calendar.

fields.name: location
fields.desc: Geographic location of the calendar as free-form text. Optional. Read-only.

fields.name: method
fields.desc:
The method used to deliver the notification. Possible values are:  
- "email" - Reminders are sent via email. 
- "sms" - Reminders are sent via SMS. This value is read-only and is ignored on inserts and updates. SMS reminders are only available for G Suite customers.

fields.name: type
fields.desc:
The type of notification. Possible values are:  
- "eventCreation" - Notification sent when a new event is put on the calendar. 
- "eventChange" - Notification sent when an event is changed. 
- "eventCancellation" - Notification sent when an event is cancelled. 
- "eventResponse" - Notification sent when an event is changed. 
- "agenda" - An agenda with the events of the day (sent out in the morning).

fields.name: fileId
fields.desc:
ID of the attached file. Read-only.
For Google Drive files, this is the ID of the corresponding Files resource entry in the Drive API.

fields.name: fileUrl
fields.desc:
URL link to the attachment.
For adding Google Drive file attachments use the same format as in alternateLink property of the Files resource in the Drive API.

fields.name: iconLink
fields.desc: URL link to the attachment's icon. Read-only.

fields.name: mimeType
fields.desc: Internet media type (MIME type) of the attachment.

fields.name: title
fields.desc: Attachment title.

- "freeBusyReader" - The user has read access to free/busy information. 
- "reader" - The user has read access to the calendar. Private events will appear to users with reader access, but event details will be hidden. 
- "writer" - The user has read and write access to the calendar. Private events will appear to users with writer access, and event details will be visible. 
- "owner" - The user has ownership of the calendar. This role has all of the permissions of the writer role with the additional ability to see and manipulate ACLs.

fields.name: defaultReminders

fields.name: groupExpansionMax

Specific reason for the error. Some of the possible values are:  
- "groupTooBig" - The group of users requested is too large for a single query.

optinalQueryParams.name: syncToken
optinalQueryParams.desc:
Token obtained from the nextSyncToken field returned on the last page of results from the previous list request. It makes the result of this list request contain only entries that have changed since then.
If the syncToken expires, the server will respond with a 410 GONE response code and the client should clear its storage and perform a full synchronization without any syncToken.
Learn more about incremental synchronization.
Optional. The default is to return all entries.
